<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  EXAMPLE ONLY - DO NOT INSTALL FROM THIS LEAF.

  launchd alternative for the EOD meeting-sync fire (design Phase 5, Decision
  7a). The design's PREFERRED trigger is CronCreate (harness routines): "one
  mechanism per surface: cron owns the trigger, nothing else does." This plist
  is the long-lived launchd alternative, shipped UNINSTALLED. Register the
  schedule (cron OR launchd) ONLY after a hand-run proves one real meeting cycle
  (design Phase 5); until then the schedule stays off.

  SLOT IDENTITY: the run computes its own slot from the fire date ($(date +%F)),
  so this entry always processes TODAY's eod slot. Stage A is slot-scoped, so a
  fixed fire never grabs "the newest doc"; it selects that slot's PT window.

  TIMEZONE: launchd StartCalendarInterval fires in LOCAL time. Confirm the host
  is America/Los_Angeles (`sudo systemsetup -gettimezone`) before trusting the
  hour, because classification hinges on the 13:00 PT morning/eod boundary
  (Decision 7a / TZ-DST). The run also self-defends: it converts fire-time to PT
  and re-derives its slot rather than trusting the label.

  MODE (propose): the scheduled path runs REAL up to the PROPOSAL: fetch the
  slot's notes (bin/fm-gfetch.sh), run the Stage B extraction
  (bin/fm-msync-extract.sh, a headless scoped claude turn), build the
  change-list, and post the proposal to the tracker-sync board thread for
  David's ONE okay. THE CADENCE NEVER AUTO-APPLIES: applying stays behind
  David's okay (the tracker-sync gate), and FM_MSYNC_SCHEDULED=1 makes
  fm-meeting-sync.sh structurally REJECT the apply flag (exit 2), so a
  mis-edit here cannot flip autonomy on.

  DEPENDENCY: the meeting ingest needs bin/fm-gfetch.sh credentialed (open
  question 10). Absent a credential the run takes the honest degrade: it posts
  ONE loud "paste the notes / fix the credential" line to the tracker-sync
  board thread (deduped in state, one post per slot) and exits 3; this launchd
  job then logs that and is a safe no-op, never a crash and never silent.

  INSTALL (only at the Phase 5 gate):
    1. Edit the absolute paths below to the real firstmate checkout.
    2. cp docs/launchd/com.firstmate.meeting-sync-eod.plist.example \
         ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.firstmate.meeting-sync-eod.plist
    3. launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.firstmate.meeting-sync-eod.plist
    4. Verify: launchctl list com.firstmate.meeting-sync-eod
  RE-INSTALL after this template changes: launchctl unload the installed plist,
  re-copy, launchctl load again (launchd never re-reads a changed file).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>Label</key>
  <string>com.firstmate.meeting-sync-eod</string>
  <key>ProgramArguments</key>
  <array>
    <string>/bin/bash</string>
    <string>-lc</string>
    <string>FM_MSYNC_SCHEDULED=1 /Users/dq4443/dev/personal/firstmate/bin/fm-meeting-sync.sh --slot "$(date +%F)/eod" --propose</string>
  </array>
  <key>StartCalendarInterval</key>
  <dict>
    <key>Hour</key><integer>21</integer>
    <key>Minute</key><integer>0</integer>
  </dict>
  <key>StandardOutPath</key>
  <string>/Users/dq4443/dev/personal/firstmate/data/meeting-sync-audit/meeting-sync-eod.log</string>
  <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
  <string>/Users/dq4443/dev/personal/firstmate/data/meeting-sync-audit/meeting-sync-eod.err</string>
  <key>RunAtLoad</key>
  <false/>
</dict>
</plist>
